Reports from British consular officials and various Russian newspapers on the wave of anti-Semitic rioting that swept the Russian Empire in 1881. There are reports on all the major incidents, as well as some analysis of the causes of the disturbances and the motivation of the rioters. The general apathy of the Russian authorities is criticized with a few honourable exceptions made.
